             was indicted for <rs id="t17270412-48-off231" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17270412-48-off231" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17270412-48-off231" type="offenceSubcategory" value="forgery"></interp>
               Forgery, in drawing up a Counterfeit Writing, in order to receive the Pay of 
                     <persName id="t17270412-48-victim316" type="victimName">
                        William 
                        Bar 
                     <interp inst="t17270412-48-victim316" type="surname" value="Bar"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17270412-48-victim316" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17270412-48-victim316" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                   
               
                  </rs>, Deceas'd. It appear'd that the Prisoner was one of those vile Persons, who makes a Practice of drawing up false Powers, and Letters of Administration, and thereby cheating and defrauding the Widows of such Seamen as die in the Voyage. This Fact in particular was proved upon her, that she forged a Will in the Name of 
               <persName id="t17270412-48-person317">
                  William
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="172704120008"></xptr> But<interp inst="t17270412-48-person317" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17270412-48-person317" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , on board his Majesty's Ship the Mary; to which Will she annex'd a Probate, and filled it up in the Name of the Archbishop of Canterbury. In her Defence: She pleaded a great deal of Ignorance, Innocence, and Incapacity, yet she talk'd of Administrations, Probates, and broad Seals. with as much Dexterity as if the had been educated at Doctors Commons. The Jury brought her in <rs id="t17270412-48-verdict232" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17270412-48-verdict232" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               guilty
            </rs>.</p>
